Review summary: All five candidate services showed mild anomalies, but carts exhibited the strongest and most consistent signals: multiple KPIs (cpu, latency-50/90, socket, workload, mem) exceeded their per-component P95 during the incident window, and carts.log.row_count had a pronounced spike. No error_count spikes or trace/error_log data were available. The earliest significant CPU breach for carts occurred at 2024-01-19 08:57:00 UTC, and CPU showed the largest deviation from baseline. Therefore the most likely root cause is carts experiencing high CPU usage.

